\textit{Source: [Stacks Project], Modules on Ringed Spaces,
  Lemma~\texttt{lemma-stalk-tensor-product}.}
  The forward half of the stalk--tensor commutation \cref{lem:stalk_tensor_commutation}
  is assembled from four maps. For a neighbourhood \(U \ni x\), the \(R(U)\)-balanced
  bilinear map \(\mathtt{stalkTensorBilin}\colon A(U) \times B(U) \to A_x \otimes_{R_x}
  B_x\), \((a,b) \mapsto \mathrm{germ}_x a \otimes \mathrm{germ}_x b\), descends through
  the neighbourhood colimit to the additive comparison map \(\mathtt{stalkTensorDesc}
  \colon (A \otimes^{p} B).\mathtt{stalk}\,x \to A_x \otimes_{R_x} B_x\); its
  \(R_x\)-linear repackaging is \(\mathtt{stalkTensorLinearMap}\), and the descent of the
  \(R_x\)-balanced dual bilinear map (\cref{def:rev_bihom}) is the candidate inverse
  \(\mathtt{stalkTensorRev}\). Together these are the underlying maps of the isomorphism
  \cref{lem:stalk_tensor_commutation}.

